2)First create a range from 1 to 8. Then using zip, merge the given list and the range together to create a new list of tuples.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
z=['a','b','c','d','e','f','g','h','i']
l=[]
for i in range(1,9):
    wlw=int(input())
    l.append(wlw)
print(l)
print(list(zip(z,l)))
23
32
34
43
34
5
5456
6
[23, 32, 34, 43, 34, 5, 5456, 6]
[('a', 23), ('b', 32), ('c', 34), ('d', 43), ('e', 34), ('f', 5), ('g', 5456), ('h', 6)]

